skin.skin_des_1200502: [Summer Vibes (Dorabella)] Arriving at the beach, Dorabella decides to take a relaxing vacation. She sets up a parasol and lays out food and drinks on the table. A gentle breeze blows, and the waves lap at the shore, bringing a satisfied smile to the mage's face.
skin.skin_des_2200402: [Mystic Melody (Marina)] Free from the curse and regaining her voice, Marina is filled with aspirations and hopes. She offers the Mystic Melody for her departed kin amidst the ruins of the Ocean Temple.
skin.skin_des_5400402: [Dangerous Summon (Aiushtha)] For Aiushtha, exuding deadly charm is as easy as drinking water. But this is the beach, too many hormones, and watchful rivals! She has to show her real skills. With a snap of her fingers, she summons her "old friends", the loyal Abyss minions. When the succubus goes all out, who dares stand in her way?
skin.skin_des_5100302: [Nightmare Assault (Dullahan)] Dullahan's army once conquered Palmarius, and the gruesome history he authored continues to haunt countless families. Even today, on Halloween, people still lock their doors and windows, fearing the rebirth of the abyssal nightmare under the bat-filled, moonlit sky, a creature hungering for blood and on the prowl.
skin.skin_des_5301002: [Azure Reaper (Ariana)] Red and black are the loneliness of the hunter and killer hidden in the dark night; blue and white are the blessing of the oath to give her a new life. When the dust and smoke cleared, Ariana's flying scythe was no longer a murderous weapon for hunting, but a sharp blade for guarding the oath.

skin.skin_des_1300302: [Jinglebell Gunmaiden (Catrina)] Catrina's dictionary has never known the word "surrender," and it is her resilience that has led her to achieve her current success. skin.skin_des_3200102: [Twinkle Bliss (Allie)] In Ellie's heart, red was once the color of loved ones' deaths; now, pure friendship has shown her that red can also bring warmth. She wants to pass this warmth on to other children, but her generous ways don't seem to be widely accepted. She still can't distinguish what kind of red can make people feel warm...
